    "body": "### Problem\n\nWrong display when deleting line with inline virtual text causes another line to wrap:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/35768171/44818e37-325c-41d4-afc3-69a102b0a9bc\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Run `nvim --clean`\r\n2. Source the following file:\r\n```vim\r\ncall setline(1, ['aaa', 'bbb', 'ccc', 'ddd', 'eee'])\r\ncall setline(3, repeat('c', winwidth(0) - 1))\r\nlet ns = nvim_create_namespace('')\r\ncall nvim_buf_set_extmark(0, ns, 1, 0, #{virt_text: [['!!!']], virt_text_pos: 'inline'})\r\n```\r\n3. Press `j`\r\n4. Press `dd`\r\n5. The last two lines are both displayed as `eee`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe last two lines are displayed as `ddd` and `eee`\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.10.0-dev-2294+gc0b99bb1de   \n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A (deletes text property with line)\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.31.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
